<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/951</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Japanese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tanaka</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-14"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                        1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January
                                        15</hi>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Under instructions from Viscount
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MI1">Motono</persName> I have the honor to
                                acquaint you for your strictly confidential information that the
                                Imperial Government have recently decided upon the dispatch of two
                                warships, <hi rend="italic">Asahi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Iwami</hi>, to Vladivostok for the purpose of affording
                                protection in case of emergency to the resident Japanese <pb facs="0118" n="28" xml:id="pg_28"/> and Allied subjects and
                                citizens and that the <hi rend="italic">Iwami</hi> was to have
                                arrived there on the 13th instant.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">T.
                                    Tanaka</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>